      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "We need to know the solubility at different temperatures because the ability of a solute to dissolve in a solvent can change with temperature. For example, sodium nitrate dissolves more in water at higher temperatures than at lower ones. This is mainly because heating increases the movement of water molecules, helping to break down the solute faster. Can you think of a time when temperature changes might affect something you dissolve?"
    },
